4JMA.F.summary: Jumia Technologies AG operates an e-commerce platform in Africa, Portugal, Germany, and the United Arab Emirates. The company's platform consists of marketplace that connects sellers with consumers; logistics service that enables the shipment and delivery of packages from sellers to consumers; and payment service, which facilitates transactions to participants active on the company's platform in selected markets. Its marketplace offers various products in a range of categories, such as fashion and apparel, beauty and personal care, home and living, fast moving consumer goods, smartphones, and other electronics, as well as access to various services, including restaurant food delivery, hotel and flight booking, classified advertising, airtime recharge, and instant delivery. The company was formerly known as Africa Internet Holding GmbH and changed its name to Jumia Technologies AG in January 2019. Jumia Technologies AG was founded in 2012 and is headquartered in Berlin, Germany.

ART.DE.summary: artnet AG, through its subsidiary, Artnet Worldwide Corporation, operates an online resource for the international art market worldwide. It operates through Artnet Galleries, Artnet Price Database, Artnet Auctions, and Artnet News segments. The artnet Galleries segment presents artworks from member galleries and partner auction houses online. This segment represents approximately 1,100 galleries presenting approximately 245,000 artworks by approximately 23,300 artists internationally. The Artnet Price Database segment consists of database-related products, including the Price Database Fine Art and Design and the Price Database Decorative Art; market alerts; and analytics reports. The Artnet Auctions segment provides a platform to buy and sell artworks online. The Artnet News segment offers a platform for the events, trends, and people that shape the art market, as well as provides up-to-the-minute analysis and commentary in cultural journalism. artnet AG was incorporated in 1989 and is headquartered in Berlin, Germany.

BTBB.DE.summary: Sleepz AG, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an e-commerce company in Germany. The company operates online shops that sell sleep products, including beds, box springs, slatted frames, mattresses, beddings, and sleeping accessories, as well as home and living products. Its online shops include perfekt-schlafen.de, markenschlaf.de, schlafnett.de, matratzenunion.de, schlafhandel.de, onletto.de, bettenriese.de, and buddysleep.de. The company also develops mattresses under the Grafenfels brand. The company was formerly known as bmp Holding AG and changed its name to Sleepz AG in August 2017. Sleepz AG was founded in 1997 and is based in Berlin, Germany.

DEX.DE.summary: Delticom AG, together with its subsidiaries, operates as an online distributor of tires and automotive accessories in Germany and Europe. Its focuses on selling tyres and wheels online. The company sells its tires to retail and commercial customers for passenger cars, motorbikes, trucks, utility vehicles, buses, and wheel sets. The company operates 440 online shops and online distribution platforms in 75 countries. Delticom AG was founded in 1999 and is based in Hanover, Germany.

H24.DE.summary: home24 SE, together with its subsidiaries, markets, sells, and ships furniture and home furnishings in Europe and Brazil.
